				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Song upgrades, what upgrades?<a name="15258"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jan 12 04 1:40 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>I just noticed this misinformation.
<br />

<br />
<blockquote><b>Quote:</b><br><span class="quote">at lvl 60 our chants max damage is 42, at lvl 65 our chant damage is 42</span></blockquote>
<br />

<br />
Without an instrument mod:
<br />
The max damage of the sub 60 chants is 33.
<br />
The max damage of the post 60 chants is 42.
<br />

<br />
With max AAs and an elemental instrument:
<br />
The max damage of the sub 60 chants is 133.
<br />
The max damage of the post 60 chants is 170.
<br />

<br />

<br />

<br />
Let's do some math.
<br />

<br />
If you can maintain all 5 post 60 chants on a mob, you will be doing 850 per tick (142 dps).
<br />
If you can maintain all 4 sub 60 chants plus Fufil's, you will be doing 620 per tick (103 dps)
<br />

<br />

<br />
I don't know about you, but in my reality a 40% dps increase between 60 and 65 is pretty impressive.
<br />

<br />
Another thing to keep in mind is that bards can sustain this DPS indefinately as we are not tied to manapool and mana regen limitations.
<br />

<br />

<br />

<br />
You also mentioned our 'shield' songs a number of times... could you elaborate on that? What songs are you talking about?
<br />
</span></td>
