<br />
That you posted earlier, And I can see where you are coming from I think anyway, how we dont get a boost at healing and dmg output per sec... as much as other classes do. But consider for healing Chorus of marr, thats 20hp a tick to everyone in a raid. Say you have a small raid of 18 people... thats 360hp per tick to the raid without epic. Now take a dru/pal/clr and have them heal even just that 20hp to every person in the raid not only would it take more than a tick but it would cost mana and quite a bit of it im sure. But bards cannot really be compared by hp per sec to healers because it has always been my view that although over the course of a night a bard will heal more raw HPs than any healer, but healers can do it when someone is about to die, which sets them appart.But back to the point, the other graph thing that caught my attention was this 
